      "text": "Discussion: For most of human history, the ability to walk between destinations was a key requirement of all cities. But especially in the last half-century, many portions of cities have become unwalkable, often because the design of vehicular facilities has disrupted pedestrian movement. This condition is not sustainable, given the correlation with high rates of resource consumption, depletion, pollution, and other impacts of an unwalkable lifestyle.1,2",
